To start gnome terminal maximized
1) go to /usr/share/applications
2) Find a file called org.gnome.Terminal.desktop
3) Set `Exec=gnome-terminal --window --maximize`

In order to get vim to use system clipboard
1) you need to use a package that was copiled using clipboard support (vim --version | grep clipboard) --> +clipboard
2) if it's -clipboard -> install vim-gtk3
3) set clipboard=unnamedplus
4) now the system clipboard is used for yank/paste by default

Had an issue with getting virtualbox installed on Ubuntu because SecureBoot was enabled
solution was to sign some virtualbox packages
https://devicetests.com/install-virtualbox-uefi-secure-boot-ubuntu
